theorem closure_inter_closure_subset_inter_closures
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure ((A ∩ closure (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := by
    have h_subset : ((A ∩ closure (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy; exact hy.1
    exact (closure_mono h_subset) hx
  have hxB : (x : X) ∈ closure (B : Set X) := by
    have h_subset : ((A ∩ closure (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure (B : Set X) := by
      intro y hy; exact hy.2
    exact (closure_mono h_subset) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB

theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_interiors {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (interior (B : Set X)) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `A ∩ interior B` is contained in `A`
  have hA : ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ A := by
    intro y hy
    exact hy.1
  -- `A ∩ interior B` is contained in `interior B`
  have hB : ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ interior (B : Set X) := by
    intro y hy
    exact hy.2
  -- Close the inclusions
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) :=
    (closure_mono hA) hx
  have hxB : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (B : Set X)) :=
    (closure_mono hB) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB

theorem P1_P2_P3_of_full_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : interior (A : Set X) = Set.univ) :
    Topology.P1 A ∧ Topology.P2 A ∧ Topology.P3 A := by
  -- First, show that `A = univ`, since `interior A ⊆ A`.
  have hA_univ : (A : Set X) = Set.univ := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro x hxA
      have : (x : X) ∈ interior (A : Set X) := interior_subset hxA
      simpa [h] using this
    · intro x _; exact Set.mem_univ _
  -- Reduce the goal to the already proved fact for `univ`.
  simpa [hA_univ] using (Topology.P1_P2_P3_univ (X := X))

theorem closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_union_left
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior (A ∪ B)) := by
  -- First, note that `interior A ⊆ interior (A ∪ B)`.
  have hInt : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) := by
    apply interior_mono
    intro x hx
    exact Or.inl hx
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  exact closure_mono hInt
